children.text: The smoke detector in this location has been installed too close to the wall, which is not in accordance with the BCA.
Part 3.7.5.5 Installation of smoke alarms requirements of the Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘Where a smoke alarm is located on the ceiling it must be a minimum of 300 mm away from the corner junction of the wall and ceiling’ .
This incorrectly installed smoke detector must be relocated so it is installed in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
